params.accessManager: Address of the access control manager.

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to query.

returns._0: True if the token is active, false otherwise.

isConsumingScheduledOp().details: Returns true only in the context of a delayed restricted call, at the moment that the scheduled operation is being consumed. Prevents denial of service for delayed restricted calls in the case that the contract performs attacker controlled calls.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

register(address,uint256).details: Requires approval before an asset can be registered.

params.assetId: The unique identifier for the asset, serving as the NFT ID.
params.to: The address that will own the minted NFT.

revoke(uint256).details: This action is irreversible and restricted to governance control.

params.assetId: The unique identifier of the asset to be revoked.

setAuthority(address).details: Transfers control to a new authority. The caller must be the current authority.

returns._0: True if the contract supports the given interface.

switchState(uint256).details: If the asset is active, it becomes inactive; if inactive, it becomes active.

params.assetId: The ID of the asset whose state is being changed.

returns.newState: The updated state of the asset (`true` for active, `false` for inactive).

params.assetId: The unique identifier of the asset being transferred.
params.to: The address of the new owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

ASSET_REFERENDUM().notice: Reference to the asset verification contract for content approval.

constructor.notice: Disables initializers for security reasons in UUPS upgradeable contracts.

isActive(uint256).notice: Check if a token is in an active state.

register(address,uint256).notice: Registers a new asset as an ERC721 NFT.

revoke(uint256).notice: Revokes an asset, permanently disabling it within the system.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Checks if the contract supports a specific ERC standard interface.

switchState(uint256).notice: Switches the activation state of an asset.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfers an asset to a new owner.
